data.enText: a fault in sth or a disadvantage of sth
the merits and demerits of the scheme
a mark on sb's school record showing that they have done sth wrong

data.chText: 在校内抽烟一经发现将被记过失分三分。
data.enText: You'll get three demerits if you're caught smoking on school grounds.

tr: the quality of being inadequate or falling short of perfection
example: they discussed the merits and demerits of her novel
he knew his own faults much better than she did

tr: a mark against a person for misconduct or failure
usually given in school or armed forces
example: ten demerits and he loses his privileges

value.def: The demerits of something or someone are their faults or disadvantages.

example.ex: ...articles debating the merits and demerits of the three candidates.
example.tran: 就 3 位候选人的优缺点进行辩论的文章
